dard Specifications M 41-10 Page 2-15 2-03.3(14)C Compacting Earth Embankments This section describes three methods (A, B, and C) for building earth embankments. The Contractor shall use Method B unless the Special Provisions require another method. Method A – Each embankment shall be made of layers no more than 2 feet thick. The Contractor shall compact each layer by routing loaded haul equipment over its entire width. If the Engineer approves, the Contractor may use end dumping to begin placing a side hill fill too narrow for hauling equipment. When the fill is wide enough, the remaining layers shall be compacted by the loaded hauling equipment. Method B – The top 2 feet of each embankment shall be compacted to 95 percent of the maximum density as determined by the[[SRC_1]][[SRC_2]]

