- Signs and plaques larger than those shown in Tables 2C-1 and 2C-2 may be used (see Section 2A.11).
- The minimum size for all diamond-shaped warning signs facing traffic on exit and entrance ramps at major interchanges connecting an Expressway or Freeway with an Expressway or Freeway (see Section 2E.11) should be the size identified in Table 2C-1 for the mainline roadway classification (Expressway or Freeway). If a minimum size is not provided in the Freeway column, the Expressway size should be used. If a minimum size is not provided in the Expressway column, the Single Lane size should be used.
- Except as provided in Section 2A.07, the sizes for warning signs shall be as shown in Table 2C-1.
- The use of warning signs shall be based on an engineering study or on engineering judgment.
- Warning signs shall be retroreflective or illuminated (see Section 2A.21).
- Except as provided in Paragraph 2 of this Section or unless specifically designated otherwise, all warning signs shall be diamond-shaped (square with one diagonal vertical) with a black legend and border on a yellow background.
- The minimum sign and plaque sizes for signs specific to bicycle-only facilities and shared-use paths shall be those shown in Table 9A-1. These sizes shall be used only for signs and plaques installed specifically for bicyclist applications.
- Any diamond-shaped warning sign that is placed such that it is applicable only to bicyclists or pedestrians on shared-use paths or separated bicycle lanes may be 18” x 18”.
- The use of warning signs should be kept to a minimum as the unnecessary use of warning signs tends to breed disrespect for all signs. In situations where the condition or activity is seasonal or temporary, the warning sign should be removed or covered when the condition or activity does not exist.
