PROMPT 70: What are MUTCD requirements for flagger hand signal procedures?
======================================================================
RESPONSE:
- Use of flags should be limited to emergency situations.
- Flags, when used, shall be red or fluorescent orange-red in color, shall be a minimum of 24 inches square, and shall be securely fastened to a staff that is approximately 36 inches in length.
- The free edge of a flag should be weighted so the flag will hang vertically, even in heavy winds.
- When used at nighttime, flags shall be retroreflectorized.
- Flaggers shall use a STOP/SLOW paddle, a flag, or an Automated Flagger Assistance Device (AFAD) (see Sections 6L.02 through 6L.04) to control road users approaching a TTC zone.[[SRC_1]]

